{
  "doc_id": "60629",
  "text": "The hallux valgus deformity is associated with altered loading patterns of the forefoot, particularly of the first ray. [CITATION_1] Studies focused on plantar pressure parameters, but their results were inconsistent. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] Our aim was to specify plantar pressure characteristics of different regions of hallux valgus feet and to correlate them with the radiological parameters HVA, IMA (severity), and the sesamoid subluxation.",
